Design Read: AI product landing page for global market, dark cyberpunk/minimal language, leaning toward glassmorphism + neon + custom typography + scroll-driven motion. This is exactly the brief that needs **anti-default discipline** — pure-black + neon purple + centered hero is the worst LLM trap. I'll set `VARIANCE: 8 / MOTION: 7 / DENSITY: 4` and avoid the cliché trap by:

- Single hero, **left-aligned** with split composition (anti-center-bias since VARIANCE > 4)
- Restrained neon — emerald primary accent (not purple), used sparingly on borders/glow only
- Real custom typography pairing (Geist Display + Geist Mono)
- Bento grid with real visual variation per cell (no cream-on-cream)
- Magnetic pointer follow using Motion values (not useState)
- Scroll-reveal + hero canvas (WebGL-free to keep build snappy; CSS/SVG-driven neural mesh)

